526
00:39:44,788 --> 00:39:47,450
How long has it been
since you stopped writing?

527
00:39:49,092 --> 00:39:50,787
About a month.

528
00:39:51,895 --> 00:39:54,598
Do you remember
the first thing you wrote?

529
00:39:54,598 --> 00:39:56,266
A poem.

530
00:39:56,266 --> 00:39:58,427
A poem. About what?

531
00:39:58,735 --> 00:40:00,259
My dad.

532
00:40:00,904 --> 00:40:02,806
Can you remember anything it said?

533
00:40:02,806 --> 00:40:05,366
I told you, I don't wanna
talk about my childhood.

534
00:40:09,044 --> 00:40:12,347
I just... I feel so stupid,
sitting in therapy.

535
00:40:12,347 --> 00:40:14,783
People have much harder
childhoods than mine.

536
00:40:14,783 --> 00:40:17,649
We're not talking about others.
We're talking about you.

537
00:40:18,153 --> 00:40:20,321
I'll give her that much.

538
00:40:20,321 --> 00:40:22,312
I'm the problem.

539
00:40:24,759 --> 00:40:27,361
I worry about being in therapy.

540
00:40:27,361 --> 00:40:30,331
I worry about not being in therapy.

541
00:40:30,331 --> 00:40:33,662
I even worry I'm not entertaining
enough for Dr. Sterling.

542
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:37,536
I just keep thinking that
if I could just be normal...

543
00:40:37,536 --> 00:40:41,674
...if I could just get out of bed in the
morning, everything would be okay.

544
00:40:41,674 --> 00:40:43,574
Well, what do you think normal is?

545
00:40:46,179 --> 00:40:50,081
Most people, they cut themselves,
they put a Band-Aid on, keep going.

546
00:40:50,416 --> 00:40:51,644
And what do you do?

547
00:40:52,418 --> 00:40:53,749
I just keep bleeding.

548
00:40:54,387 --> 00:40:58,155
So you think being normal is having
a wound, putting a patch on it...

549
00:40:58,155 --> 00:40:59,679
...then go on with your life?

550
00:41:00,691 --> 00:41:02,249
Isn't that what functioning is?

551
00:41:03,127 --> 00:41:05,296
Isn't that what living is?

552
00:41:05,296 --> 00:41:08,365
You know, you keep going,
no matter what happens to you.

553
00:41:08,365 --> 00:41:10,230
Is that the way you wanna live?

554
00:41:37,459 --> 00:41:39,120
Mom.

555
00:41:41,163 --> 00:41:43,427
Oh, come on, now, honey.

556
00:41:43,732 --> 00:41:47,791
Why don't you tie up your hair
anymore? Your face is so pretty.

