00:41:51,304 --> 00:41:53,238
Here they are.

558
00:41:59,779 --> 00:42:01,508
Come on, now, Lizzie.

559
00:42:08,021 --> 00:42:10,783
Hi, honey!

560
00:42:14,425 --> 00:42:16,585
Is she home yet?

561
00:42:25,537 --> 00:42:29,803
I need someone to shut off my brain
and turn on my heart.

562
00:42:30,508 --> 00:42:35,544
Well, I have long brown hair,
dark eyes.

563
00:42:35,544 --> 00:42:38,414
You probably meet tons of
girls in the men's bathroom.

564
00:42:38,414 --> 00:42:41,941
Oh, yeah, the Ecstasy goddess.

565
00:42:42,552 --> 00:42:45,621
Yes, I can't believe
you remember that.

566
00:42:45,621 --> 00:42:47,088
Lizzie.

567
00:42:50,293 --> 00:42:52,284
Can you hang on a sec?

568
00:42:53,196 --> 00:42:55,398
Grandma and Grandpa are here.

569
00:42:55,398 --> 00:42:56,763
Yes, I heard.

570
00:42:58,232 --> 00:43:03,761
You know, the only reason I threw a
birthday party was to make you happy.

571
00:43:05,472 --> 00:43:08,609
I don't understand how you can
treat me like this.

572
00:43:08,609 --> 00:43:10,304
Can I have some privacy, please?

573
00:43:20,521 --> 00:43:22,282
That was my mother.

574
00:43:22,688 --> 00:43:26,225
It's my birthday.
She's throwing this big party for me.

575
00:43:26,225 --> 00:43:27,926
Cool.

576
00:43:27,926 --> 00:43:30,622
Well, no, actually, it's not.

577
00:43:30,963 --> 00:43:33,899
It's just me and my mother
and my grandparents.

578
00:43:33,899 --> 00:43:35,588
I haven't even been out there yet.

579
00:43:35,588 --> 00:43:37,453
Aren't they missing you?

580
00:43:37,790 --> 00:43:40,092
Well, now you sound like
a nice Jewish boy.

581
00:43:40,092 --> 00:43:43,083
Well, I might, if I was Jewish.

582
00:43:44,195 --> 00:43:46,595
I just wanted to call and say hi.

583
00:43:47,966 --> 00:43:50,368
Let's meet up when
you get back to school.

584
00:43:50,368 --> 00:43:52,570
Okay, that'd be great.

585
00:43:52,570 --> 00:43:55,903
Hey, happy birthday.

586
00:43:58,043 --> 00:43:59,601
Thank you.

587
00:44:02,080 --> 00:44:04,047
Rafe didn't seem to realize...

588
00:44:04,047 --> 00:44:07,074
...he'd just been appointed
to save my life.

589
00:44:09,720 --> 00:44:12,355
Rolling Stone magazine.

590
00:44:12,355 --> 00:44:15,491
It's the music magazine.

591
00:44:15,491 --> 00:44:18,895
That's wonderful, honey.

592
00:44:18,895 --> 00:44:23,799
They want her to work for them. Yeah.
Paid work for Rolling Stone.

593
00:44:24,367 --> 00:44:25,800
They'll pay her?

594
00:44:32,641 --> 00:44:36,009
I think she was up writing
late last night.

595
00:44:36,979 --> 00:44:39,003
Were you up writing late last night?

596
00:44:39,814 --> 00:44:41,680
I haven't written anything in months.

597
00:44:42,984 --> 00:44:45,454
She's always working on something.

598
00:44:45,454 --> 00:44:47,656
She just doesn't like to talk about it.

599
00:44:47,656 --> 00:44:49,454
Like you've ever read any of it.

600
00:44:55,463 --> 00:44:57,598
Lizzie, this isn't very nice.

601
00:44:57,598 --> 00:44:59,226
You want one?

602
00:45:09,141 --> 00:45:12,077
What's wrong with her?

603
00:45:12,745 --> 00:45:15,648
Nothing. Ma, nothing's wrong with her.

604
00:45:15,648 --> 00:45:18,351
- She's drunk.
- Of course I'm drunk.

605
00:45:18,351 --> 00:45:21,821
- She's just tired.
- She's as skinny as a ghost.

606
00:45:21,821 --> 00:45:24,119
She's overtired.
They work so hard up there.

607
00:45:25,691 --> 00:45:27,819
- Lizzie.
- Is she on drugs?

608
00:45:28,695 --> 00:45:31,230
- I wish I was on drugs.
- Lizzie.

609
00:45:31,230 --> 00:45:33,199
- Did she say that she...?
- No, Ma.

610
00:45:33,199 --> 00:45:35,733
It's okay. Everything is okay.

611
00:45:35,733 --> 00:45:38,971
Mom, believe me,
if I was on drugs, I'd tell you.

612
00:45:38,971 --> 00:45:42,074
People don't behave this way
if they're not on drugs.

613
00:45:42,074 --> 00:45:44,474
I fucking do.

614
00:45:55,719 --> 00:45:58,153
I'm so sorry, Mama.

615
00:46:07,897 --> 00:46:11,400
I dream about all the things
I wish I'd said.

616
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:14,538
The opposite of what
came out of my mouth.

617
00:46:14,538 --> 00:46:18,140
I wish I'd said,
"Mom, please forgive me.

618
00:46:18,140 --> 00:46:20,276
Please help me.

619
00:46:20,276 --> 00:46:23,575
I know I have no right
to behave this way."

620
00:46:36,992 --> 00:46:39,060
- Hello.
- Hey.

621
00:46:39,060 --> 00:46:42,264
- Hi.
- How' my birthday girl?

622
00:46:42,264 --> 00:46:44,665
You're late. You're a day late.

623
00:46:44,665 --> 00:46:46,964
What can I say, you know how it is.

624
00:46:47,235 --> 00:46:51,306
Anyway, I thought I'd have to be
dealing with your secretary by now.

625
00:46:51,306 --> 00:46:54,741
You're such a bigshot journalist,
writing for Rolling Stone.

626
00:46:54,741 --> 00:46:56,710
- Did you read it?
- You know...

627
00:46:56,710 --> 00:46:59,109
...remember this,
they're lucky to have you.

628
00:47:00,046 --> 00:47:02,950
These guys, they're smart.
They're really smart.

629
00:47:02,950 --> 00:47:05,619
They know what they're doing.
They can see talent.

630
00:47:05,619 --> 00:47:08,722
I'm probably gonna get assignments
all over the country...

631
00:47:08,722 --> 00:47:10,824
...so I could maybe come visit you.

632
00:47:10,824 --> 00:47:12,814
Who are you talking to, Lizzie?

633
00:47:14,493 --> 00:47:16,996
- It's no one.
- Who is it?

634
00:47:16,996 --> 00:47:18,898
- It's no one.
- Don't listen to her.

635
00:47:18,898 --> 00:47:20,365
Please, Mom.

636
00:47:21,767 --> 00:47:24,103
Look at you, the two of you.

637
00:47:24,103 --> 00:47:26,505
- Go on, you're so in love with him.
- Mom.

638
00:47:26,505 --> 00:47:28,840
Can you hear that?
Hear why I don't call?

639
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:30,575
Where was he your childhood?

640
00:47:30,575 --> 00:47:32,669
- Where...?
- Stop it! Just stop it!

641
00:47:35,214 --> 00:47:37,883
I just wanted to talk to him!

642
00:47:37,883 --> 00:47:40,477
You know, Lizzie,
I'm at the end of my rope.

643
00:47:43,321 --> 00:47:47,257
I've been working extra hours.
I never go out.

644
00:47:47,657 --> 00:47:51,685
I never buy clothes.
I spend all our money on your therapy.

645
00:47:52,963 --> 00:47:55,362
All our money? Daddy pays, Mom.

646
00:47:55,698 --> 00:47:57,665
You think he pays?

647
00:47:58,868 --> 00:48:01,132
You think he's paying?

648
00:48:01,537 --> 00:48:04,707
He doesn't pay one cent.

649
00:48:04,707 --> 00:48:08,733
Not one single red cent!

650
00:48:09,678 --> 00:48:11,613
That's not true.

651
00:48:11,947 --> 00:48:15,417
Oh, you want me to show you?
Huh? You wanna see?

652
00:48:15,417 --> 00:48:20,156
You want to see how much I'm paying,
still paying...

653
00:48:20,156 --> 00:48:22,924
...on your last term bill? Huh?

654
00:48:22,924 --> 00:48:25,893
Here. Here, look at these.
Look at these.

655
00:48:25,893 --> 00:48:28,997
- There, look at that, Lizzie.
- I'm sorry, Mom.

656
00:48:28,997 --> 00:48:33,525
You wanna see how much
I'm paying this Dr. Sterling?

657
00:48:33,835 --> 00:48:35,237
I'm sorry.

658
00:48:35,237 --> 00:48:37,739
No, you're not gonna
talk your way out of this.

659
00:48:37,739 --> 00:48:40,606
Ask her who pays her!

660
00:48:43,345 --> 00:48:47,447
You know, it's my fault,
for spoiling you the way I did.

661
00:48:47,447 --> 00:48:51,985
I kill myself to get you to Harvard, and
you come back looking like a zombie.

662
00:48:51,985 --> 00:48:54,818
I know. I'm sorry.

663
00:48:55,788 --> 00:48:57,313
I'm so...

664
00:48:58,090 --> 00:49:00,150
Why won't he?

665
00:49:01,961 --> 00:49:04,929
- Why won't he?
- I know. I know, honey. I know.

666
00:49:06,565 --> 00:49:10,636
I hate myself,
and I hate the things I do.

667
00:49:10,636 --> 00:49:13,606
Lizzie, it's all right. It's all right.

668
00:49:17,209 --> 00:49:19,540
It's awful. It's so awful.

669
00:49:21,979 --> 00:49:25,184
And I hurt the people who love me.

670
00:49:25,184 --> 00:49:28,050
But when he calls...

671
00:49:34,692 --> 00:49:36,716
My God, a party?

672
00:49:37,128 --> 00:49:40,290
And your stupid pear tart!

673
00:49:47,704 --> 00:49:49,272
Why do you do this, Lizzie?

674
00:49:49,272 --> 00:49:53,071
Because I'm not
your goddamn monkey!

675
00:49:57,680 --> 00:50:01,740
I'm sorry, Mom, I didn't mean it.
I'm sorry.

676
00:50:02,385 --> 00:50:04,410
I didn't mean it.

677
00:50:05,920 --> 00:50:07,786
I'm sorry.

678
00:50:16,498 --> 00:50:18,932
She threw the party for herself?

679
00:50:20,201 --> 00:50:21,836
No, I guess for Grandma.

680
00:50:21,836 --> 00:50:24,168
Why would she want to do that?

681
00:50:27,175 --> 00:50:29,938
To show her what
a good little girl she was.

682
00:50:30,812 --> 00:50:32,779
That must really hurt.

683
00:50:33,848 --> 00:50:38,284
Look at her.
This isn't a breakthrough, darling.

684
00:50:38,786 --> 00:50:42,152
My mom pays $ 100 an hour for this.

685
00:50:43,489 --> 00:50:48,895
This is the same bullshit. Insight time.
It's like that stuff with that guy Rafe.

686
00:50:48,895 --> 00:50:52,165
I don't have to be Freud to know
I have a fear of rejection.

687
00:50:52,165 --> 00:50:55,101
And I know where it comes from.
I know it's from my dad.

688
00:50:55,601 --> 00:50:58,137
But it doesn't change anything.

689
00:50:58,137 --> 00:51:01,163
- I still can't go out with him.
- Why not?

690
00:51:01,673 --> 00:51:03,198
I just told you.

691
00:51:05,877 --> 00:51:08,346
You didn't tell me
anything about Rafe.

692
00:51:08,848 --> 00:51:11,645
Has he ever given you reason
to believe he'd reject you?

693
00:51:21,359 --> 00:51:23,589
Do not show him how crazy you are.

694
00:51:25,095 --> 00:51:27,431
- A monkey?
- Called Percy.

695
00:51:27,431 --> 00:51:29,133
I know, it beats me.

696
00:51:29,133 --> 00:51:31,901
- She needed someone to talk to.
- Well, she had you.

697
00:51:31,901 --> 00:51:33,493
No, no, this was before.

698
00:51:33,837 --> 00:51:36,328
- Are you listening?
- God, yes.

699
00:51:36,673 --> 00:51:37,970
I'm not boring you?

700
00:51:38,375 --> 00:51:41,009
Please, Lizzie.
I met you in a men's room.

701
00:51:41,009 --> 00:51:44,377
- You're anything but boring.
- What am I?

702
00:51:46,316 --> 00:51:48,147
Scary.

703
00:51:49,686 --> 00:51:52,177
So are we gonna go to this gig?

704
00:51:53,922 --> 00:51:55,480
I'm not sure.

705
00:51:56,492 --> 00:51:58,427
I don't really know where it is.

706
00:51:58,427 --> 00:52:01,591
You came to see a gig,
and you don't know where it is?

707
00:52:02,198 --> 00:52:05,496
I said I came to see the gig...

708
00:52:08,470 --> 00:52:10,199
You know.

709
00:52:11,106 --> 00:52:15,043
- What?
- Okay, now you're just being cruel.

710
00:52:15,043 --> 00:52:16,677
No, no, you said...

711
00:52:16,677 --> 00:52:20,546
I said I came to see the gig...

712
00:52:21,715 --> 00:52:24,412
...but I came to see you.

713
00:52:44,971 --> 00:52:48,202
Waiting, waiting, waiting.

714
00:52:49,742 --> 00:52:52,710
Waiting for him to make the move.

715
00:52:55,848 --> 00:53:00,809
Doesn't he know?
He' gotta be my salvation.

716
00:53:09,527 --> 00:53:11,763
It' lovely that he' caring...

717
00:53:11,763 --> 00:53:14,961
...compassionate
and politically correct.

718
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:17,801
But I need him to kiss me.

719
00:53:17,801 --> 00:53:19,702
Right now.

720
00:54:06,047 --> 00:54:08,038
Ruby!

721
00:54:08,818 --> 00:54:10,648
Ruby.

722
00:54:16,123 --> 00:54:17,386
Hey.

723
00:54:17,658 --> 00:54:19,421
Hey.

724
00:54:19,692 --> 00:54:23,493
I didn't know you'd moved rooms.
I thought you were still in here.

725
00:54:25,633 --> 00:54:29,124
Ruby was telling me about
those articles you're planning to write.

726
00:54:30,737 --> 00:54:33,467
That stuff's always
been easy for me.

727
00:54:37,878 --> 00:54:40,546
Dr. Sterling must have called him.

728
00:54:40,546 --> 00:54:42,945
Why else would he be here?

729
00:54:43,448 --> 00:54:46,652
Probably to see how dire
the situation is.

730
00:54:46,652 --> 00:54:49,416
See if his little girl can
get through the day still.

731
00:54:50,189 --> 00:54:51,918
Or...

732
00:54:52,392 --> 00:54:55,484
...maybe he really did finally miss me.

733
00:54:56,495 --> 00:54:57,756
My girl.

734
00:55:00,832 --> 00:55:03,001
Dad, you know those medical bills?

735
00:55:03,001 --> 00:55:05,526
The ones for the psychiatric
treatment?

736
00:55:07,506 --> 00:55:09,674
They keep sending them to Mom.

737
00:55:09,674 --> 00:55:12,404
So I guess you haven't paid.

738
00:55:12,811 --> 00:55:16,312
- I can't believe you're asking me this.
- Oh, you have paid?

739
00:55:16,312 --> 00:55:18,416
You're all cold and distant.

740
00:55:18,416 --> 00:55:20,351
And... And...

741
00:55:20,351 --> 00:55:23,086
And now you're asking me what?

742
00:55:23,086 --> 00:55:24,620
What are you talking about?

743
00:55:24,620 --> 00:55:28,425
- If you don't know...
- No. No, I don't know.

744
00:55:28,425 --> 00:55:32,262
- You made a promise.
- You haven't written me.

745
00:55:32,262 --> 00:55:34,397
You never call me.

746
00:55:34,397 --> 00:55:36,699
It's like I don't even exist.

747
00:55:36,699 --> 00:55:41,370
- Who do you think you're talking to?
- I even come and visit you.

748
00:55:41,370 --> 00:55:43,305
- Fuck you!
- You watch that language!

749
00:55:43,305 --> 00:55:45,874
- Is that a way to talk to your father?
- Listen.

750
00:55:45,874 --> 00:55:49,679
You're the one who left. You're the one
who walked away for four years.

751
00:55:49,679 --> 00:55:52,914
You think I don't know that?
Is that what you think?

752
00:55:52,914 --> 00:55:54,649
